<Content>A place to return to time and time again Recently, my girlfriends and I decided to celebrate a birthday by staying overnight at a Boston hotel. Familiar with the Boston Harbor Hotel, I suggested we stay there. Our stay was one of the most memorable times - the service, ambience, food and atmosphere is unparalleled. The employees of the hotel are so kind and they really do make you feel at home once you step into the hotel. The hotel's lobby is gorgeous, the fresh flowers are stunning. We ate dinner in Intrigue Cafe - a comfortable cafe that boasts a rare view of Boston Harbor. The next morning, we ate brunch in Meritage and it was wonderful. You could choose anything from gourmet omelettes to sushi! The Boston Harbor Hotel is one of the best places I have stayed in a long time. I am so happy to have this hotel close by so I can visit time and time again. A must see! 
