<Content>Boston Harbor Hotel, first class all the way! We stayed at the Boston Harbor Hotel for one night after the Simon and Garfunkel concert. When we checked in, we were very impressed, the lobby was beautiful but not pretentious. There is very easy access to the warf outside which would have been wonderful if it wasn't so chilly the night we stayed! The conceriege was great, they made reservations for us the following morning for their buffet brunch (best brunch I EVER had!). We went up to our room, which was a skyline view and WOW it was pretty! The rooms are very large sized and since we got the cheapest room, we weren't expecting much. We had a nice view of Boston (and the big dig, hehehe). The bed was soooo comfy, they had robes, and slippers. Plus very nice soaps and shampoos. The mini bar was stocked with anything from peanuts to champagne! When we got back from our concert we found the bed turned down and our robes and slippers laid out for us. Overall, it was a great experience!! 
