<Content>A Slice of Heaven in the Middle of Boston Being in my late 20s, and of the Sex and the City era, I tend to gravitate towards boutique hotels with trendy interiors and happening bars. I decided to try the Boston Harbor Hotel on the recommendation of a good friend. I was immediately impressed with the hotel from the time I pulled up to the front of the property. The broad exterior exudes strength and high class, and the doormen couldn't have been more helpful. Stepping into the hotel, one is immediately struck with the feeling of comfort. The regal lobby is small, yet grand in it's own right, and I found myself walking a little taller on my way to the front desk. Check in was smooth and quick, the way I like it. The staff was courteous and attentive.Upon entering my room, I fell in love with the two room suite! I felt like I had my own apartment in the city. The view from the room was fantastic, with large windows looking out over the Harbor. I arrived late, and was pleasantly surprised to find my bed turned down, and bathrobe and slippers laid out for me. After my bags were delivered to my room, I slipped downstairs for dinner and drinks at Meritage, the fantastic wine restaurant that my friend had raved about.I only stayed the weekend, but would definitely come back again. Everything was perfectm, the Hotel itself, the staff, the location, the food!! I would definitely recommend this hotel to anyone who is looking for an extraordinary experience in Boston. 
